  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nThe current benchmarks use an [impromptu API](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/master/scripts/benchmark/utils/chain_plumbing.py) to create the chains that are used for benchmarking.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nWe now have some more solid [builder tools](https://py-evm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api/eth/tools/api.tools.builders.html) to create chains. These tools allow the creation of chains using a declarative, fluent API which we do use already in several tests.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/3061a48d112b2ae7d94adec89000372dd4bcac2c/tests/core/chain-object/test_chain_reorganization.py#L9-L17\r\n\r\nWe should be able to use the same tools to either use them in each benchmark directly and get rid of `chain_plumbing.py` altogether or, if that still turns out too boilerplatey, at least cleanup `chain_plumbing.py` to use the builder tools underneath.",
